description:
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you possess excellent administration and IT skills?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Are you committed to providing an efficient and effective administrative service?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Have you been a team player who possesses experience of team working coupled with an ability to act on your own initiative to support your team.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Do you wish to be part of a dynamic innovative organization that offers agenda for change (AFC) terms and conditions with employee benefits?&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If so you might be the person we are looking for…&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;As an NHS provider of community health services, Nottingham CityCare exists to support the health and wellbeing of all local people, working alongside other health and care partners to achieve this. We are values driven, people business with a passion for excellence. Our vision and social purpose is to build healthier communities and our values of integrity, expertise, unity and enterprise lie at the heart of everything we do, guiding how we work together with partners and each other to consistently deliver high quality compassionate care. As a social enterprise we aim to add social value by investing in the future of our local communities and helping to make a difference in people’s lives.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Nottingham CityCare’s Child Health team are a NHS England commissioned service, administering&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Child Health information systems, (CHIS). These systems provide and maintain a clinical record for&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;every child and support a variety of Child Health and related activities, including universal services for&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;population health and support for statutory functions such as immunisations and childhood screening. Child Health are looking to recruit an administrator support person on a permanent basis to join their&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;busy team. The post holder will be responsible for providing a comprehensive administrative and&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;clerical service to the Child Health team which includes but is not limited to:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting the development of data and information management systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Gathering and accurately collecting data and information from a variety of sources relating to service performance at team level.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Taking minutes at meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Arranging and coordinating meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Establishing and maintaining effective local clerical systems including electronic and manual filing systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Photocopying, processing referrals, scanning and attaching patient related information to patient records&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Supporting diary management.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is essential that you possess the ability to communicate effectively with a range of people at all levels both within and outside of Child Health and Nottingham CityCare, either in person or on the telephone, promptly and in a professional and courteous manner whilst recognising barriers to communication. You must also be able to demonstrate an ability to deal sensitively with the needs of all who may experience communication barriers for example where English is not their first language.&lt;/p&gt;
